                                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-lg"></i> Bird watching enthusiasts can also visit Kokrebellur Pelicanry, which is a small village near Bheemeshwari.</li>
                                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-lg"></i> Sangam is the confluence of rivers Cauvery and Arkavathi. It is a popular picnic spot.</li>
                                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-lg"></i> Continue your exploration of nature at Galibore just 14 kilometers away.</li>
                                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-lg"></i> About an hour away is Doddamakali which is considered a natural haven.</li>
                                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-lg"></i> Muthathi is only about 5 minutes from Bheemeshwari and is another famous spot among tourists.</li>
                                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-lg"></i> Don’t miss Chunchi water falls, which is also pretty close to the resort.</li>
                                    <li><i class="bi bi-check-lg"></i> Mekedatu is one place that never fails to amaze tourists through its breath-taking landscapes.</li>
